The paper discusses a distributed query engine for analytical database workloads, which suggests that it belongs to the database (cs.DB) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The paper also focuses on the two levels of networks in modern database clusters, which suggests that it belongs to the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses load imbalances and scalability issues, which suggests that it belongs to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents a novel communication multiplexer, which suggests that it belongs to the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
